#### [Amaneunsis](https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/1070159-amanuensis)
*Transmutation cantrip*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 Action
- **Range:** 30 ft
- **Components:** S, M (a quill and inkwell)
- **Duration:** 1 Hour
- **Classes:** Bard, Cleric, Wizard
---
While holding a quill you move your hand as though writing in the air. You manipulating the written word creating one of the following effects:
- You instantly cause nonmagical text of up to 250 words from one source to be copied into a book, or onto a piece of paper or parchment. The spell does not translate the copied writing. If you do not understand the original, you have no additional ability to understand the copy.
- You create an invisible magical sensor in the air that records all speech within 30 feet into a book, or onto a piece of paper or parchment for 1 hour. 
- You touch an item containing some form of text and speak a word or phrase. For 1 hour, all references to that word or phrase glow luminously where present.
- You instantly copy a single illustration on a page or piece of parchment, limited to the color of the ink used in the material component.
- You animate a book giving it a mouth and voice to read its pages aloud for 1 hour. The voice speaks in the language in which the book is written. 
- You instantly repair a faded page of text returning it to legibility. The spell has no effect on a magic book, spell scrolls or spell books. The spell does not translate the writing.

If you cast this spell multiple times, you can have up to three of its non-instantaneous effects active at a time, and you can dismiss such an effect as an action.


#### Bardcraft
*Illusion cantrip*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 Action
- **Range:** 30 feet
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** ?
- **Classes:** Bard
---

You can alter different aspects of your voice for 10 minutes. These chances may include: the rate you speak, your pitch, articulation, pronunciation, and fluency. Alternatively, you can mimic a voice that you have heard before.
You can choose an empty space within range that you can see, and for 10 minutes your voice is heard as if it were coming from that space instead of you.
Choose an instrument within range that you are proficient with and is not being held by another creature, to become animated for 10 minutes. While animated, the instrument can play a tune on your behalf, and can be up to three times as loud. If the instrument weighs less than 10 pounds, it can hover up to 10 feet off the ground and can move up to 30 feet as a bonus action. If you have multiple instruments animated, each instrument can be moved as part of the same bonus action.
Choose a creature that you can see within range, to create a beam of light that illuminates the creature for 1 minute. An unwilling creature must make a Dexterity saving throw to avoid the spell. If the creature is willing or fails the saving throw, a beam of light appears to come from a direction of your choice and illuminates the area around the creature with a bright light around the creature and creates dim light for an additional 5 feet. If the chosen creature moves, the light will follow the creature up to 15 feet before the light disappears.

ou reinforce your vocal cords, allowing you to sing in unnaturally high and low notes for 1 hour. 
You apply magical makeup to enhance your beauty and cover up any marks or blemishes for 1 hour. 
You instantly clean, press and mend an article of clothing. Any damage you mend cannot be greater than a missing button or a slight tear in the fabric. 
You create an instantaneous, harmless sensory effect to enhance a performance, such as a shower of sparks, small fireworks or confetti. The effect must fit in a 5-foot cube.

